<h2 class="wp-block-heading faq-heading">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>



<div class="schema-faq wp-block-yoast-faq-block"><div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1623393125914"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Can you build legs with just body weight?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Yes, you can build your legs with just <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/bodyweight-leg-exercises" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">bodyweight leg exercises</a>. You can build muscle size by appropriate <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7927075/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">loading for muscle hypertrophy</a>. This can be done through increasing reps and sets or by adding weight to the exercise.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1732156877342"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Should I train my legs as a beginner?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Yes, you should train your legs. The legs are a large muscle group that is valuable for activities of daily living. Building your legs, regardless of training status, will help with daily functionality.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1732156877787"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Is 30 minutes enough for legs?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Yes, 30 minutes is sufficient for exercising your legs as long as you maximize your reps and sets you can perform for each exercise.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1732156878429"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Is 3 leg days too much?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">No. You can exercise your legs three days each week as long as you allow yourself<a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30036284/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow"> 24–48 hours</a> to recover between sessions. This allows for additional benefits for your muscles to build strength.</p> </div> </div>
